Basic German grammar is presented, vocabulary is studied and simpler topics are discussed (me, my family, everyday life, school, theatre, giving directions etc.). The study materials are the readers from German speaking countries with audio cassettes. Pronunciation, analytical reading, and use of dictionaries are trained. The course is aimed at the participants without any preliminary knowledge of German.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to attain CEF level A1.2. This course focuses on the development of the following skills:
reading, writing and listening.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course the students know-how to: - use everyday courtesies greetings and addressings;  - communicate actively in everyday situations;  - read simple texts using a dictionary.
